title: About Me
text:
My goal is to be a Wildlife Biologist for the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation! New York is my home state, so I would love to go back there and work.



I graduated with my bachelors degree in Biology from the University at Albany, and now I am pursuing my masters in Wildlife and Conservation Biology at the University of New Hampshire.



I previously worked as an Environmental Intern and then as the Climate Change Program Manager for the Seneca Nation Environmental Protection Department.
Thanks for checking out my web site!
